    Message when supplied type is wrong

    msg_wrongType.Rd

    Message when supplied type is wrong

    Usage

    msg_wrongType(
  arg,
  req_type = c("char", "num", "date_char"),
  mode = c("col", "val", "no_typeof"),
  name = NULL,
  data = NULL,
  ...
)

    Arguments

    arg

    Preset column name or argument for which the validation is run.

    req_type

    Type that was expected for this arg.

    mode

    Defines if validation is done for a column (col) or for a single value scalar (val). This will determine how the current wrong type of the supplied column or vector should be evaluated. The no_typeof option is for when we do not need the message to print the type of the supplied input.

    name

    Only for modes col and val. The column name, supplied as deparse(substitute(argument)) or input value as substitute(argument).

    data

    A dataframe. Only for mode col.

    ...

    Additional argument passed to msg_result().

    Value

    Prints a message to the console.

    Examples

    msg_wrongType("age", req_type = "num", mode = "no_typeof")
#> 

#> ✖ age must be an unquoted name of a numeric column or a number scalar.
